  <prompt>
    Create a BFF endpoint POST /api/workspace/matters/pre-fill that accepts uploaded files (multipart/form-data),
    stores them temporarily via SpeFileStore, analyzes them using the AI Playbook (document analysis), and returns
    pre-filled matter form field values. The AI extracts: matter type, practice area, matter name, organization,
    estimated budget, key parties, and summary from the uploaded documents. The endpoint is rate-limited to
    prevent AI abuse.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Expert in .NET 8 Minimal API file handling, multipart form data processing, SpeFileStore facade for SPE file operations, AI Playbook document analysis via PlaybookService, and structured data extraction from AI responses.</role>

  <goal>
    A working BFF endpoint at POST /api/workspace/matters/pre-fill that accepts multipart/form-data with file
    uploads, stores files via SpeFileStore, calls the AI Playbook for document analysis, extracts structured field
    values from the AI response, and returns a PreFillResponse with matter field values. The endpoint validates
    file types and sizes, is rate-limited, and returns ProblemDetails on error. It builds without errors.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      The AI pre-fill endpoint is a key productivity feature for the Create New Matter wizard. When users upload
      documents in Step 1 (contracts, engagement letters, invoices, etc.), Step 2 calls this endpoint to have
      the AI analyze the documents and suggest field values for the matter record. This reduces manual data entry
      from ~5 minutes to ~30 seconds of review. The endpoint handles file upload storage (via SpeFileStore facade
      per ADR-007), AI document analysis (via PlaybookService per ADR-013), and structured extraction of matter
      field values from the AI response.
    </background>
