  <steps>
    <step order="1">Add pre-fill endpoint to WorkspaceEndpoints: MapPost("/matters/pre-fill", HandlePreFill) — accepts multipart/form-data with IFormFileCollection</step>
    <step order="2">Create PreFillResponse record with extracted field values: matterType (string?), practiceArea (string?), matterName (string?), organization (string?), estimatedBudget (decimal?), keyParties (string?), summary (string?), confidence (double), preFilledFields (string[] — list of field names that were successfully extracted)</step>
    <step order="3">Implement file validation — reject files that are not PDF/DOCX/XLSX (by extension and content type), reject files larger than 10MB. Return 400 ProblemDetails with specific validation errors per file.</step>
    <step order="4">Store uploaded files temporarily via SpeFileStore — use temporary container or staging area. Files are stored for AI analysis and later associated with the matter record (in task 024 Finish flow).</step>
    <step order="5">Call AI Playbook (PlaybookService) for document analysis — pass file content/references with a prompt instructing extraction of: matter type, practice area, matter name, organization, budget, key parties, and summary. Use structured output format if supported by PlaybookService.</step>
    <step order="6">Parse AI response and extract structured field values — map AI output to PreFillResponse fields. Track which fields were successfully extracted in preFilledFields array. Handle partial extraction gracefully (some fields null).</step>
    <step order="7">Add rate limiting — same policy as task 026 (10 requests per minute per user). Return 429 ProblemDetails when exceeded.</step>
    <step order="8">Verify dotnet build succeeds with no errors or warnings</step>
    <step order="9">Update TASK-INDEX.md — mark task 028 as complete</step>
  </steps>

